After that, the similarities end. The Cold War was more of a political struggle for power than it was an all-out war like WWII. There were no actual battles between the two main opponents in the Cold War. Because of this, the smaller countries of the world played a much more important part in the Cold War.here are many similarities between the Cold War and the Second World War, but there are many more differences. WWII was a much more traditional or hot war.
